Code organization and naming conventions---
alwaysApply: true
---
- File naming: controller.*.js, behavior.*.js, config.*.js, lib.*.js, service.*.js, utils.*.js, prototype.*.js
- Controllers use PascalCase class names (ControllerGame, ControllerRoom)
- Behaviors use camelCase (behavior.harvest.js â†’ "harvest")
- Constants use UPPER_SNAKE_CASE (CONSTANTS.CPU.BUCKET_CRITICAL)
- Private methods use underscore prefix (_rooms, _cache)
- All modules must export using module.exports
- Use JSDoc comments for all public methods with @param and @returns
- Group related functionality in the same file
- Keep files focused on a single responsibility
